items.name: Motorcycle (No sidecar)
items.description: A motorbike without a side-car. A new vehicle will be coming in May.

items.name: Motorcycle (w/ sidecar)
items.description: A trials-style motorbike equipped with a side-car. It allows three passengers and is the fastest vehicle in the game, currently. It has very good traction to the road, however, it can be flipped easily and currently kills all passengers instantly if they fall off of it. It has very low fuel consumption, at least half the current rate of the other vehicles in-game.

items.name: Buggy
items.description: The Buggy is an open frame vehicle with a smaller engine than the Jeep or other vehicles. Though the engine is smaller, the frame is much lighter, meaning the buggy is relatively fast, albeit insecure due to the lack of wall panels or other such armoring.

items.name: Sedan
items.description: a passenger car in a three-box configuration with A, B & C-pillars and principal volumes articulated in separate compartments for engine, passenger and cargo

items.name: UAZ
items.description: The UAZ is like a hybrid between the Buggy and the Jeep. A light frame wraps almost entirely around, with only the back compartment exposed. The vehicle is quite fast, but less protective against small arms. The vehicle is very prone to being damaged, though, so it can be destroyed really quickly on the road - additionally, fuel consumption when at full throttle is quite high, which negates much of the benefit of the vehicle. It's best used off-road, moving between locations, though it should be turned off near populated areas so you don't give yourself away with its sound.

items.name: Jeep
items.description: The Jeep is a mid-sized, closed frame vehicle that is entirely closed from the exterior area. Because of this, it provides superior defense against small arms.

items.name: Speed Boat
items.description: The speedboat is a relatively quick moving craft, but there's a huge trade off as the boat has no cover or protection against ranged attacks. Because of this, while it's a great vehicle for navigating coastal features (and especially dealing with constricting play area), it is very dangerous to operate.

items.name: Truck
items.description: The vehicle is yet to be represented as a usable vehicle since it was first introduced.

items.name: Blue circle of death
items.text:
Blue circle of death gets smaller over time. And be minimize after 32.26:
 Circle 1 - Time: 00:00 - DPS: 0.5 - Radius: ~2.25 Km
 Circle 2 - Time: 11:52 - DPS: 0.75 - Radius: ~1.5 Km
 Circle 3 - Time: 17:41 - DPS: 1 - Radius: ~0.9 Km
 Circle 4 - Time: 21:41 - DPS: 1.5 - Radius: ~0.36 Km
 Circle 5 - Time: 24:33 - DPS: 3 - Radius: ~0.18 Km
 Circle 6 - Time: 27:15 - DPS: 5 - Radius: ~0.08 Km
 Circle 7 - Time: 29:15 - DPS: 7.5 - Radius: ~0.04 Km
 Circle 8 - Time: 31:11 - DPS: 11 - Radius: ~0.015 Km
 Circle 9 - Time: 32:26 - DPS: 11 - Radius: 0 Km

- The Bandage need 4s to cast so you need atleast (DPS * 4) Health to recover 10 Health overtime.
- The First Aid Kit need 7.5s to cast so you need atleast (DPS * 7.5) Health to recover 75 Health instantly.
- The Med Kit need 10s to cast so you need atleast (DPS * 10) Health to recover 100 Health instantly.

items.name: Game story
items.text: BATTLEGROUNDS takes place on the main island (Erangel), an abandoned Russian island where a military occupation was controlling it. The military occupation tested chemical/biological experiments on the islands population, after a resistant attack on a biological facility, the island had to be abandoned.

items.name: Control
items.text:
MOVEMENT:

Forward: W
Back: S
Left: A
Right: D
Crouch: C
Prone: Z
Jump: SPACE
Sprint: SHIFT + W
Walk: CTRL + W
Auto Run: =
Prone Roll: Q / E
Switch Views: Q / E

 VEHICLE CONTROLS:

Forward: W
Back: S
Left: A
Right: D
Handbrake: SPACE
Boost: SHIFT + W / S
Switch Seat: CTRL + 1 / 2 / 3 / 4

 VIEW:

1st/3rd Person Toggle: V
Aim: Right-Click Hold
Scope/ADS View Toggle: Right-Click Once
Hold breath (1st person only): Shift

 WEAPONS:

Reload: R
Fire-mode Toggle: B
Switch Weapon: 1-5 Number Keys (1-Primary 'Right side weapon, 2-Secondary 'Left side weapon, 3-Pistol, 4-Melee, 5-Grenade)
Cycle Weapons: Scroll Up/Down
Next weapon: G
Change zeroing: Page Up / Page Down

 OTHER CONTROLS:

Open/Close/Get-in/Get-out/Pickup: F
Medical and Boost items: 7,8,9 & 0
Split Items: CTRL + Drag item off screen
Push to Talk: T
Voice chat mute/un-mute: CTRL + T
Toggle UI: CTRL + U
Inventory: TAB / I
Map: M
Free look: ALT + Mouse Move
Quick Looting: Right click
